HEADWORD: Scleroderm
<hw>Scler"o*derm</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>sklhro`s</grk> hard + <grk>de`rma</grk> skin: cf. F.
<ets>scl⟦eacute⟧roderme</ets>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of a tribe of plectognath fishes (<fam>Sclerodermi</fam>)
having the skin covered with hard scales, or plates, as the cowfish and
the trunkfish.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the Sclerodermata.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>Hardened, or bony, integument of various
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scleroderma</ent>⟦br⟧
